## Direction change: mainline kernel

The linux-sunxi.org page for the RG35XX H reveals mainline support is much further along than expected.

As of kernel 6.10, merged into mainline:
- RG35XX H device tree (`sun50i-h700-anbernic-rg35xx-h.dts`)
- WiFi: RTW88 8821CS driver
- AXP717 PMIC
- Display engine DE33 (patches submitted May 2025)
- Gamepad buttons and thumbsticks
- Power LED

WIP but functional with patches:
- Mainline U-Boot at `git.sr.ht/~tokyovigilante/u-boot`
- LCD display (NV3052C driver)
- Mali GPU via Panfrost

This changes the plan significantly. We are switching from KNULLI blobs to mainline U-Boot plus a recent mainline kernel. This means:

- No more squashfs. Standard ext4 rootfs.
- No more KNULLI boot chain. Proper sunxi U-Boot + extlinux boot.
- RTL8153 ethernet will work (r8152 is mainline).
- WiFi will work via RTW88.
- Display is close to working.

The build script needs rewriting for the mainline approach. The Buildroot rootfs stays, just the boot chain changes.

